One fuction of the operating system is the security. The security pevent use of applications and programs from unauthorized individuals. This is done primarily by requiring a password to be entere.
A second function of the operating system is the proccesor management. This is also called process scheduling. It acts as a traffic controler when and how long to process.
A third fuction is the support for buiilt-in utility programs. This function searches and detects errors within the operating system. Not only does it detect the issues, but it fixes them.
